</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-24_ pf-text-1">The Equality Act 2010 legally protects people from discrimination in the workplace and wider society, covering nine protected characteristics including age, disability, gender reassignment, race, religion or belief, sex, sexual orientation, marriage and civil partnership, and pregnancy and maternity.
































